            <p>Synagogue Chambers&#44; Iyar 16<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5614<lb/>
                Philad. May 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1854<lb/>
                My Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>It affords me pleasure to inform<lb/> you that at a meeting of the Board of<lb/> Managers of K. K. M. I. held this morning<lb/> It was Resolved unanimously that leave<lb/> of absence be granted you to visit your father<lb/> &#38; family immediately after the ensuing Holidays<lb/> until the middle of September next.&#42;<lb/>  Trusting that you may have a safe<lb/> and speedy voyage&#44; a Happy meeting<lb/> with your family&#44; and that we may<lb/> have the pleasure of greeting you on<lb/> your return in the enjoyment of health<lb/> &#40;in which my dear wife joins&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>I remain Revd. Sir<lb/>
                Yours Very Truly<lb/>
                Revd. S. Morais<lb/>										
                Hazan of the Congregation<lb/>								
                A. Hart.<lb/>
                Parnass<lb/>
                &#34;Mickve Israel&#34;<lb/>
                &#42; Your Salary will of course go on the same as if you were<lb/> here&#44; during your absence.<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
